tue.yellow

Class Patient

  • java.lang.Object
    • tue.yellow.Patient

  • public class Patient
extends java.lang.Object
    Patient is the class for all patients that enter and have entered the emergency department. Patients interact with many different other objects (classes), for example doctors, nurses, beds, chairs, etc.
    Author:
    Team Yellow

    • Constructor Detail

      • Patient

        public Patient(java.lang.String name,
               java.lang.String complaints,
               Patient.TriageUrgency triageUrgency,
               Bed.Zone triageZone,
               ListTracker lt)
        Creates a patient object using 5 input values:
        1) Name of the patient
        2) Complaints of the patient
        3) Triage urgency of the patient (IMMEDIATE, VERY_URGENT,URGENT,STANDARD,NON_URGENT)
        4) Triage zone of the patient (TRAUMA/NO_INJURY)
        5) List (emergency room) to which the patient belongs
        This constructor adds the patient to the list of the emergency room upon creation.

        The current status of the patient after the object creation is ENTERED_ER, and the health status is SICK. The new patient is not yet assigned to any resource (doctor, nurse, bed or chair). If a triage urgency is already know (and corresponds to a value from the Manchester Triage System), the bed urgency is also immediately derived.

        Parameters:
        name - name of the patient
        complaints - complaints of the patient
        triageUrgency - triage urgency of the patient (corresponing to a value of the Manchester Triage System)
        triageZone - triage zone of the patient
        lt - list (emergency room) to which the patient belongs

      • Patient

        public Patient(int number,
               ListTracker lt)
        Creates a number of patient objects, all with a generic name (patient i). This method adds the patient to the list of the emergency room upon creation.

        The current status of the patients after the object creation is ENTERED_ER, and the health status is SICK. The new patients are not yet assigned to any resource (doctor, nurse, bed or chair). The triage urgency and zone are still unknown, null.

        Parameters:
        number -
        lt -

      • setTriageUrgency

        public void setTriageUrgency(Patient.TriageUrgency triageUrgency)
        Sets the triage urgency of the patient object. The triage urgency is chosen from the Manchester Triage System, and can take the following options:
        • IMMEDIATE
        • VERY_URGENT
        • URGENT
        • STANDARD
        • NON_URGENT
        After setting the triage urgency, the method setBedUrgency() is called, in order to match immediately with the appropriate bed.

        Parameters:
        triageUrgency - triage urgency of the patient object

      • getBedUrgency

        public Bed.Urgency getBedUrgency()
        Gets the bed urgency of the patient object.
        Returns:
        the bed urgency of the patient object

      • setBedUrgency

        public void setBedUrgency()
        Sets the bedUrgency of the patient. The bed urgency depends on the triage urgency. The bed urgency is URGENT if the triage urgency is:
        • IMMEDIATE
        • VERY_URGENT
        • URGENT

        The bed urgency is Not urgent if the triage urgency is:

        • STANDARD
        • NON_URGENT

      • setCurrentStatus

        public void setCurrentStatus(Patient.Status currentStatus)
        Sets the current status of the patient object. This can take several forms, which are incorporate in the methods that call upon the setCurrentStatus() method. The possibilities for current status are:
        • ENTERED_ER
        • UNDERGO_TRIAGE
        • WAITING_FOR_BED
        • IN_TREATMENT
        • IN_DISCHARGE
        • WAITING
        • BOARDING
        • LEFT_ER
        • GONE
        • IN_CHECK
        Parameters:
        currentStatus - the status of the patient at a moment

      • setCurrentBed

        public void setCurrentBed(Bed bed)
        Sets the current bed of the patient object. If the patient already has a bed, he will still be assigned to this original bed, and not to the currentBed that is given as input. This method is called by the method setAssignedPatient() in the class Bed, and cannot be called on its own.
        Parameters:
        bed - bed to which the patient is to be assigned

      • setCurrentDoctor

        public void setCurrentDoctor(Doctor currentDoctor)
        Sets the current doctor of the patient object. If the patient already has a doctor, he will still be assigned to this original doctor, and not to the currentDoctor that is given as input. This method is called by the methods that initiate treatment with a doctor, and cannot be called on its own. This method is also called to release a doctor from a patient.
        Parameters:
        currentDoctor - doctor that is assigned to the patient at a moment

        public void setCurrentNurse(Nurse currentNurse)
        Sets the current nurse for the patient object. If the patient already has a nurse, he will still be assigned to this original nurse, and not to the currentNurse that is given as input. This method is called by the methods that initiate treatment with a nurse, and cannot be called on its own. This method is also called to release a nurse from a patient.
        Parameters:
        currentNurse - nurse that is assigned to the patient at a moment

      • leaveEmergencyRoom

        public void leaveEmergencyRoom(Patient patient)
        Releases a patient from the emergency room. A patient can leave the emergency room when he is in one of the following states:
        • ENTERED_ER
        • WAITING_FOR_BED
        • WAITING
        • BOARDING
        • IN_DISCHARGE

        This means that a patient cannot leave during treatment. When a patient leaves the emergency room, the status will change into LEFT_ER, and the associated chair, bed, doctor or nurse will be released from the patient.

        Parameters:
        patient - patient that is to be released from the emergency room

      • patientDie

        public void patientDie(Patient patient)
        In the unfortunate case that a patient dies during his/her stay in the emergency room, this method is called. It changes the health status of the patient to DEAD and the current status to GONE. Furthermore, associated resources are released from the patient.
        Parameters:
        patient - patient that dies while in the emergency room

      • getViolent

        public void getViolent()
        When a patient is unsatisfied with the staff or treatment, he/she may get violent. In this case, this method is called. It will ask for a nurse to come for comfort/assistance. It will change the complains of patient by adding Violent behind.

      • callNurse

        public void callNurse(ListTracker lt)
        When a patient calls for a nurse, he/she will be added in the list of patient that have called or requested a nurse. If a patient is already assigned to a nurse, this method doesn't add the patient to the list.

      • getSicker

        public void getSicker()
        When a patient gets sicker after triage, he/she calls for another check by a nurse. It will change the complains of patient by adding Sicker behind.

      • calmDown

        public void calmDown()
        When a patient calms down, he/she will no longer be violent and the nurse will be released.
